description:
Acclaimed author JASON AARON (ASTONISHING SPIDER-MAN AND WOLVERINE, WEAPON X) and superstar artist RENATO GUEDES (Action Comics, Adventures of Superman) launch an all-new ongoing Wolverine series as Wolverine goes to hellâ€¦ literally! Someone's out to destroy Wolverine-permanently-and they may have succeeded. But if Wolverine's soul is in hell, how is his body terrorizing those closest to him?

Also included is "Last Stand of the Silver Samurai", with the titular clan leader ostensibly making his last stand to defend his clan's home.

Wolverine Goes to Hell: Part 1- Three weeks ago Wolverine and Pastor John Wraith sat on the steps of Wraith's church and discuss how Wolverine feels dammed and how Wraith feels that Wolverine has a chance to change as he has. Now, back in the present day, Wraith and his congregation are attacked by Wolverine's body possessed a demon. The possessed Wolverine kills Wraith and burns his church with everyone trapped inside. Meanwhile Melita Garner is attacked by the Mongrels, who were sent by the Red Right Hand, but she is saved by Mystique, who reveals that Wolverine's soul is in hell.

Scorched Earth Chapter 3-"Last Stand of the Silver Samurai"- The Black Samurai have been sent by the Red Right Hand to kill the Silver Samurai and destroy the Clan Yashida Ancestral Compound, but they seem to have bit off more then they could crew. The Silver Samurai fights back with everything and defeats them but his home is now ash and he has lost his life.
name: Wolverine Goes To Hell Part 1; Last Stand of the Silver Samurai Chapter One: Scorched Earth

description:
The Flintstones - A Real Oil-Osaurus - 6 pages

The Flintstones - The Hot Rock - 8 pages

The Flintstones - A Good Deal-er - 2 page text story

The Flintstones - Friends To The End! - 8 pages
name: A Real Oil-Osaurus

description: THE RACE IS ON as the Avengers, the Young Avengers, and the X-Men compete to be the first to find the Scarlet Witch. When the Young Avengers discover the secret of Wanda Maximoff's disappearance, the Avengers attempt to neutralize the Scarlet Witch before the Young Avengers can find her. But their efforts soon lead to an all-out war between the Avengers and the X-Men that only the Young Avengers can stop.

The scattered JOEs converge at their prearranged rally point and launch their last-ditch counterattack against the forces of COBRA. SNAKE EYES and STORM SHADOW face off, and only one of them walks away from the confrontation. Don't miss this issue!

volume.name: G.I. Joe: A Real American Hero

description: Mankind has fallen, civilization is extinct. All that remains are tribes of savage cannibal predators who used to be humanity's heroes. Frank Castle believes himself to be the only uninfected survivor...until he discovers that a handful of humans still live. Some are being hunted by the cannibals, others are used as pawns between warring tribes. Everyone believes that there is no one left to protect the innocent and avenge the fallen. They're wrong. The Punisher still lives, and the Last Gun on Earth is willing to wage total war to save the last humans on Earth. NY Times-bestseller Jonathan Maberry and artist Goran Parlov lock and load for the third bloody installment of this Marvel Knights event.
name: Part 3: Partner In Crime
Return to the Isle of Speech

description: From the Eisner award-winning team that brought you Daredevil, Halo, and the Avengers comes another startling new chapter in their first ever creator owned series. You've met Scarlet and now you know who she is and what she wants... the world is a corrupt broken place and she is going to fix it. But how far is she willing to go? She is talking revolution right here in the United States!! But where does one start such a thing?Â

In a radioactive, nuclear-ravaged future, Samson is born into a tribe of peaceful yet desperate people struggling to survive in the desolate city of N'Yark. Surrounded by hungry, wild creatures -- creatively mutated and brought to life by Thorne and subsequent artists -- and the more savage, selfish remnants of humanity, life is precarious at best for the tribe until Samson displays amazing powers. Discovering that young Samson is a mutant himself, his mother trains Samson to value life, and on her deathbed Samson vows "to protect the weak from the powerful, the good from the evil!"

Reprints issues of Mighty Samson (Gold Key) #1 - 6.
name: Volume One

description: As a child, Kazukiâ€™s head was filled with the stories his dad told him of another planet called Artemis. Even now that heâ€™s older and his dad has passed away, Kazuki refuses to stop believing. All he wants to do is visit Artemis, and a surprising chain of events may just give him his chance! Now Kazuki begins a quest to learn about the new world he finds himself in and the strange people he meets.
name: Vol. 1

description:
The Big Bad finally stands revealedâ€”Angel is Twilight, and it's tearing the Scoobies apart, testing the limits of their friendship.

Seems like a perfect time for Spike to come back.

Joss Whedon writes the final five issues of Buffy Season 8, taking his greatest characters to places only he can take them! Teamed with series artist Georges Jeanty, Joss counts down to the biggest Buffy final everâ€”and it starts right here!

Pic 1: Jo Chen cover

Pic 2: Georges Jeanty cover
name: Last Gleaming, Part One

volume.name: Buffy the Vampire Slayer Season Eight

name: Five Bullets for Idris the Cruel

description:
Withdrawn and seemingly fragile, Sue is a Four-Leaf Clover who possesses unique abilities. Feared by a militaristic government, she is imprisoned for her entire life to live in isolation... All of that changes when Special Agent Kazuhiko is assigned to escort the girl to the mysterious playground called Fairy Park. Coming out of retirement, Kazuhiko is ordered to to escort and protect Sue from subversive organizations that would kill to capture the "Clover" and exploit her abilities.

Chapter Titles

  • A Leaf
  • Tiny Wings in the Forest
  • The Singing Waif
  • Birdcage
  • A Maze
  • The Cat
  • A Radio
  • A Trace
  • A Debt
  • A Flower
  • Parliament
  • Clover
  • A Telephone
  • Winged Fish That Flies Through the Night
  • A Leopard
  • Back Alley
  • The Scar
  • A Song
  • Nonexistent
  • Goodnight
  • Pursuit
  • Feathers
name: Vol. 1

description: Flash back in time a year, to before Kazuhiko took Suu on her fateful journey to Fairy Park. Find out how Suu knew so much about Kazuhiko and his lover, when she spent her entire life in a cage, and discover the origin of the song that plays throughout the series.
name: Vol. 3

description: Under the thumb of a treaty that was negotiated after the Sith sacked Coruscant, the Jedi have attempted to maintain the illusion of peace-until now! Even as one battle ends on Balmorra, another begins on Dantooine, where Jedi Satele Shan finds herself clashing sabers with an enemy that threatens not just her body, but her soul! As the treaty begins to crumble around her, Satele knows something desperate must be done to save the galaxy from the return to war!
name: Threat of Peace, Part 3 of 3

description: Setting sail from a harbor choked with sunken ships, where plague victims are burned in great furnaces, Lord Baltimore reveals a terrible incident that took place during the war, where his men fell victim to creatures that feast on the freshly dead, and Baltimore himself first met the vampire who has become his obsession.
name: Part Two (of Five)

description:
Go back to the beginning with Dark Horse's 1 for $1 comics!
Â Â 
Get in on the ground floor of twelve featured titles from our popular comics pantheon. See what started it all in these first-issue classics from Dark Horse Comics.

If you thought Groo was a dangerous idiot, wait till you see how dangerous he is now that he's intelligent. Â  Â  Â

Mike Mignola has deservedly become one of the biggest names in comics for his creation of Hellboy. But when Mignola needs a short break from the Hellboy universe, he turns to diversions such as The Amazing Screw-On Head, winner of the Eisner Award for Best Humor Publication! When Emperor Zombie threatens the safety of all life on earth, President Lincoln enlists the aid of a mechanical head. With the help of associates Mr. Groin (a faithful manservant) and Mr. Dog (a dog), Screw-On Head must brave ancient tombs, a Victorian flying apparatus, and demons from a dimension inside a turnip. This new collection of oddball Mignola creations also includes "The Magician and the Snake," from Dark Horse Maverick: Happy Endings, and nearly fifty pages of brand-new material, all as weird and hilarious as the beloved Screw-On Head.
name: HC

volume.name: Amazing Screw-On Head and Other Curious Objects

description: Is the love already destroyed, in the book that IGN.com calls "A hell of a good time"? Torn and battered - and rocked by the actions taken last issue - can Hawkeye & Mockingbird even trust each other anymore? The deadly duo known as Crossfire and Phantom Rider are betting against it as they continue their bloody path of revenge! To turn the tables, our quarreling couple must put aside their differences, set their own trap, and bring in a surprise player!
name: Ghosts Part 4: Unnatural Histories

description: The thrilling conclusion to the epic â€œMickey MouseÂ on Quandomai Islandâ€ by Modern Mickey Master Casty! Minnie and Goofy have been kidnapped, and Mickey must get help from unexpected allies in order to save them. Travel with Mickey to a land beyond imagining as he unravels Quandomai Islandâ€™s greatest mystery!
name: Mickey Mouse on Quandomai Island: Part 4; Minnie Runs Out of Time part 4

description: When Jack Hawksmoor chose to board the departing Carrier, he chose uncertainty but tried to hedge his bets. Now that his terrible secret has been exposed, the loss of trust far outweighs the recent loss of life... and the loss of loved ones. But there is no time for anger or mourning. They have reached their destination. Will the Authority find the help for their dying Earth that they seek - or will the end of their journey bring new nightmares?
name: Genociety

description:
What is it that makes one an Avenger? That's what this series starring characters from all across the Avengers' history will attempt to answer! Featuring tales of Iron Man, Captain America, the Thing, Iron Fist, Justice, Firestar, Squirrel Girl, Nova and the Young Avengers and more!

Story Titles

  • The Young Avengers in "Homecoming"
  • Iron Fist and Misty Knight in "The Books of the Iron Fist"
  • Squirrel Girl in "Welcome Home, Squirrel Girl!"
  • The Pet Avengers in "Gnu Recruit"
name: Homecoming; The Books of the Iron Fist; Welcome Home, Squirrel Girl!; Gnu Recruit

description: Bubbaâ€™s back, or at least heâ€™s still here. Check out Materâ€™s new solo series as he squares off against his long-time nemesis Bubba the tow truck in the Rust Bucket Derby. Mater and Bubba are determined to answer: who is the toughest tow truck around?

volume.name: Cars: The Adventures of Tow Mater

description:
THE BATTLE FOR THE SOUL OF NEW YORK CONTINUES! The Heroic Age has begun... but Daredevil didn't get the memo. As The Man Without Fear's reign over Hell's Kitchen continues, his allies and friends come together to try and, for one last time, put an end to his rule over The Kitchen. Will the Devil's reign continue, or will the heroes triumph?

Moon Knight, still under the guise of Jake Lockley, fights his way through the dungeon of Shadowland as Ghost Rider tears through and leaves dead Hand ninjas in his wake. Moon Knight asks him why he is in Shadowland. Ghost Rider doesnâ€™t know who summoned him and he is intent on figuring out who did so.

Back at the melee from last issue, Daredevil lifts his ban on killing and calls for the deaths of all opposing him. Daredevil displays an unusually high level of martial arts skill by defeating Iron Fist and Shang-Chi. During the battle, a large explosion rocks Shadowland and Punisher enters and opens fire on the Hand. The heroes flee through the hole created by the blast and Spider-Man seals the hole to prevent pursuit by the Hand. As they leave, they notice the general populace is now out on the streets fighting and rioting, apparently affected by the same â€œdark powerâ€ affecting Daredevil.

Elsewhere, Lady Bullseye cautions Kingpin about using the zugaikotsu warrior (Ghost Rider) and tells him that Ghost Rider will come after him. Kingpin says that the scroll that summoned the warrior will also protect him from the warriorâ€™s wrath and that if Ghost Rider wants to be free of the magic that summoned him â€“ the black magic of the Hand â€“ he will have to confront the source of the magic. Kingpinâ€™s plan is to let Ghost Rider strike at the heart of the Hand and come in afterward and gain control.

Back in Shadowland, Daredevil erroneously assumes that the delegation was a diversion what went down in the dungeon. Black Tarantula begins to question Daredevilâ€™s attack on the heroes and Daredevil simply replies that they need better fighters. Daredevil instructs Typhoid Mary to follow him and bring a shovel. Moon Knight observes this conversation while hidden in the rafters. Daredevil and Typhoid Mary head to a graveyard and dig up Bullseye. Suddenly, Elektra appears and says she heard Daredevil was looking for fighters.

The heroes regroup in Harlem. Iron Fist and Shang-Chi note that Daredevil had never been capable of such martial arts prowess previously. Punisher suggests they are going to have to kill Daredevil. Master Izo appears and says he has learned the truth. The secret cadre at the heart of the Hand â€“ the Snakeroot â€“ have taken control of Daredevil and are using him as a vessel for the Beast of the Hand. The issue ends with Daredevil carrying Bullseyeâ€™s corpse, flanked by Elektra and Typhoid Mary.
name: Shadowland: Chapter 3

description: From legendary actor Samuel L. Jackson and Emmy-nominee Eric Calderon (Afro Samurai)! The conflict between the warring factions has reached critical mass, and Mulberry wants his money! Will he survive the gang warfare? Will he get the hot chick? This is the comic finale of the year with Samuel L. Jacksonâ€™s stamp of approval, so donâ€™t miss it! Covers by Dave Johnson and Jeffrey Spokes.

Uncle Sam leads the team on a quest through the hidden history of the United States! With new challenges and old threats returning to plague them, the stakes are higher than ever.

A new call to arms begins as Uncle Sam and the Freedom Fighters return in an all-new action packed ongoing series helmed by the writing team of Justin Gray & Jimmy Palmiotti with art by Travis Moore and Trevor Scott! A national mystery unfolds when the government learns of the existence of a Confederate super weapon intended to insure the South won the Civil War. Who built it and why wasn't it used? Find out when Uncle Sam leads the team on a quest through the hidden history of the United States! With new challenges and old threats returning to plague them, the stakes are higher than ever. Can even these stalwart heroes stand by their duty when their country calls?
name: American Nightmare Part One

description:
Following the disbanding of the Titans Sarge Steel meets with Roy Harper offering to solve his money troubles if he goes to Hong Kong and captures former drug Kingpin and nuclear weapons dealer Sing Lu. He quickly boards a plane and arrives in Hong Kong however he quickly notices three men following him,all of which he quickly subdues but is prevented from questioning them by the local police.He then finds a contact of Steel's Feng, who gives him an address of where to find Sing.He is quickly captured by Sing's men with Sing believing him to be an assassin sent to kill him and his daughters, however he refuses to kill Roy and instead injects him with heroin and ends up having him sent to a political prison alongside Feng until there scheduled execution by firing squad. He then begins chewing a bone from his meal sharpening it, and fakes his death as the others pass his corpse to be taken out. However he manages to use the bone to blind one man, and free the others as he begins his escape.

He then manages to escape through the sewer as all of the others quickly are sealed in and recaptured,he then makes another run at Sing as he figures that last time they had previously been tipped off to his arrival.He manages to sneak into the mansion successfully this time and begins a drawn out battle against Sing's martial artist bodyguards in the kitchen. He then arms himself with several guns and manages to make it to Sing and the two both realize they have both been lied to. Roy then returns to America and meets with Steel at the airport who gives him his check and admits to his part in the situation to motivate Roy to bring Sing in, he then unmasks Roy's "prisoner" to reveal Feng.Roy then attack Steel pulling out a knife and threatening him before leaving with Feng.
name: The Readiness To Die

description:
SHADOWLAND TIE-IN!

This ONE-SHOT takes place after DareDevil #509

and before Shadowland #3

Elektra Natchios had vowed to never again interfere in the life of her ex-lover, Matt Murdock. Learn what made her break her vow and return to Daredevil's side at Shadowland. Zeb Wells (DARK REIGN: ELEKTRA) returns to the character with hot newcomer Emma Rios (AMAZING SPIDER-MAN) for a vital piece of the Shadowland puzzle!

The Punisher and Wolverine must kill Daken! In hunting Dark Wolverine, Frank Castle has unwittingly given him the thing he needed most to complete his mission of retribution. On the rooftops of Tokyo, The Punisher, in a broken body, and his unwitting partner Wolverine, his healing factor negated, fight against a vengeful son reborn in the Exo-Mind! Dear lord is it going to get bloody.
name: Punishment Chapter 4
Gold Digger

description: The second chapter in the saga of the sole survivors of Krypton finds the entire El family adapting to their new home on Earth with varying degrees of success. Young Kal-El's become a reporter at the great Metropolitan newspaper The Daily Planet, while Jor-El clearly favors the company of the boy-genius Lex Luthor. Meanwhile, Lara's charity work covers many bases including a fateful meeting with the wealthy family that runs the Wayne Foundation. It seems the two new El family members, Bru-El and Valora, are the only ones struggling to fit in, even though they're the first Els born on Earthâ€¦
name: Part Three; Part Four

volume.name: Superman: The Last Family of Krypton

description: It's the Merc with a Mouth in a pulp caper filled with lies, spies and shapely thighs, courtesy of Mike Benson & Adam Glass (Deadpool: Suicide Kings, Luke Cage Noir) and Laurence Campbell (Punisher)! Wade Wilson. Codename: Deadpool. He's the CIA's deadliest agent. He's also certifiably insane, suffering from Multiple Personality Disorder and haunted by the ghosts of his past. In other words, he's the perfect soldier in a Cold War where it's impossible to tell friend from foe and reality from a lie. Wilson is also the only one capable of hunting down a rogue CIA agent and recovering the stolen nuclear suitcase she's carrying before she hands it over to America's enemies. But who is this femme fatale and why has she turned traitor? And is Deadpool crazy enough to survive or will he become trapped in a web of international intrigue?
name: Chapter 1

description:
Be careful what you wish for. Julie and Ivy's desperate search for Cain brings them face to face with the crazed killer, but it appears they've been led straight into a trap. Meanwhile, Foster flips a switch and the Phi super-collider is activated!

Vijay copies work off his machine and then erases the data. He walks outside and panics when Dillon approaches he blurts out that everyone on Phi is being killed and he appears to fall between two parked cars. By the time Dillon runs around from one side of the car to the other there is no sign of Vijay.

Dillon rings Ivy and tells her he's lost Vijay and notes how high her voice is. She looks in the mirror a mole on her cheek she had removed at 19 has reappeared.

They arrive at the car park and help Dillon knock out the guards and then Julie gets a terrible sense of fear when smoke appears on the horizon.

Sam C. Howe is just your average 20-something living in the big city. He has a crappy job, a run-down apartment, and a crazy roommate, but, Sam has a secret. Sam is a schizophrenic, but all of his hallucinations become real. Assuming the identity of a super-powered being called Uberman, Sam will take on the evil villian group known as the 7 Virtues, but find that the war going on inside his head may be for the wrong reasons! Â  Â
name: Strange Days

description:
Learn more about the mysterious past of King Chimera as he revisits a death he feels responsible for while in the hospital room of his fallen teammate! Then, Power Girl alone takes on the reborn gods of Parador, which may be the last thing she ever does!

And in the penultimate chapter of the co-feature, Liberty Belle is shot just as she, Hourman, Tigress and Icicle find the fabled staff of life they've been tracking as individuals and as a team!
name: Glory Days, Part 3: Apotheosis; The Inheritance, Part 9: Bad To The Bones!

description: As Nancy searches for a way out of Hell, she gains an unexpected ally: Lucifer himself! But he's not the Lucifer we're used to, and Hell is not willing to let them go... Deep in the pits, the demon called Mr. Macabre sharpens his claws as he prepares to hunt Nancy. Plus a tale of the Creation, the War in Heaven and the Fall of Lucifer, all in one issue!
name: Part 2 (of 4)

description: From Max Brooks, New York Times best-selling author of WORLD WAR Z and masterful artists Howard Chaykin and Antonio Fuso comes the next generation ofÂ G.I. JOEÂ and COBRA.
name: Dr. Mindbender; Doc
Sailor Stars 3

description: Jason Todd's journey has taken him all over the world in search of those who can help him train for his revenge on Batman. But something has begun to change inside him, and the blood and destruction he leaves in his wake is becoming far too risky. Now, he finds himself in London, learning at the feet of an expert bomber. But when Jason learns that the pyrotechnic genius is planning "something big" for the city, it may be something Jason's better nature won't tolerate...
name: Higher Learning

description: Taskmaster has trained hench-thugs for every terrorist organization and criminal cartel in the Marvel Universe. So when the rumor starts that he's turned traitor and now works for STEVE ROGERS, a billion-dollar bounty is put on his head, and every cadre of costumed fanatics -- A.I.M., Hydra, Ultimatum, the Sons of the Serpent, everyone -- looks to collect. Now Taskmaster has to fight hordes upon hordes of his psychopathic students while at the same time figuring out who framed him -- which requires him figuring out who he really is! That's right, the man with the photographic reflexes has no memory of his true identity -- and you'll learn the unexpected truth along with him!
name: The Exquisite Palace

description: Lobo returns to his old teammates for the conclusion of "The Sons of Brainiac" arc! But can even the baddest bastich in the universe beat the brains and brawn of Brainiac? Will Lobo perform the first Brainiectomy â€“ or will the Last Czarnian become just another of the villain's lab subjects?
name: Sons of Brainiac, Part 3: Brain-Drain

description: RETURN TO THE DEEP WITH MICHAEL TURNER'S FATHOM! Memories of the past come crashing into the present in this exciting all-new Aspen mini-series, FATHOM: BLUE DESCENT! Aspen Matthews is the link between the world we know and the world below, but the secrets of her past have always remained shrouded in mystery-until now! FATHOM: BLUE DESCENT journeys back to the life of Aspen's true parents, members of the underwater race known as the Blue, and the strife they encountered before she grew to become the woman we know today. An all-new cast of characters-and some familiar faces as well-kick off this exciting premiere #1 issue in dramatic fashion! With FATHOM's return at hand, some new creators and several familiar names are coming along for the ride! Taking charge of the writing chores is David Schwartz, known for his critically acclaimed Image Comics title Meltdown. Art duties for all of Aspen's curvaceous lines and intricate environments will be handled by Scott Clark of Stormwatch, Alpha Flight and X-Men fame. Together, this dynamic duo is looking forward to putting their stamp on FATHOM: BLUE DESCENT as never before! Over a decade's worth of answers spill out onto the pages of this exciting, all new FATHOM: BLUE DESCENT mini-series! Â
name: Dreams and Disappearances

description: This September, Wolverine starts down the road to hell and we want to take you along for the ride...it all starts here! With all new material by the creative teams bringing you WOLVERINE, X-23, DAKEN: DARK WOLVERINE and X-FORCE, The Road to Hell is packed with clues and signposts to help you find your way through the brand-new launch of Wolverine's own family of books! You won't want to miss it, because bonus material includes a second look at the first issue of Namor the First Mutant #1 and an exclusive preview of the November launch of an ALL NEW X-BOOK! You won't want to miss it!
name: Falling; Brace For Impact; The First Day of the Rest of Your Life

description:
Kazuki Sendo had always loved drawing and painting with his girlfriend, Mizuki Takase. But when classmate Taishi Kuhonbutsu pulls them into a doujinshi convention, Kazuki enters a whole new world. Soon he finds himself passionately drawing manga and cramming to get into conventions. As Kazuki gets acquainted with the doujinshi life style and meets new friends, he starts to drift away from Mizuki and his 'normal' way of living. Thus begins the struggle of a talented artist...

Chapter Titles

  • Party 1: Start Up!!
  • Party 2: Noisy Impression
  • Party 3: Divide In My Mind
  • Party 4: Pass Each Other
  • Party 5: Keep On Movin'! No Breaks!!
  • Party 6: Acute Sensitivity
  • Party 7: Misunderstanding
  • Party 8: Collaboration
  • Party 9: Definition of A Feasibility
  • Extra Party: Special Guest
name: Vol. 1
